        "type": "message",
        "text": "At the end of the day if the client has a strategist\/SEO who understands how to build outlines, then they'll be getting back what they want from the writer.\n\nIf the client is a founder or non-content type of person, then it's often better for the writer to interview them, build the outline\/brief for approval, and then continue forth.\n\nVery different types of engagements from the writer's perspective I think.",
